name: gain
doc: Set (query) the voltage-to-current gain setting {to z}.

name: analog_in
doc: Set (query) the analog input mode {to z=(OFF 0, ON 1)}.

name: speed
doc:
Set (query) the current source filter response speed {to z=(FAST 0,
SLOW 1)}.

name: inner_shield
doc:
Set (query) the inner-shield connection mode {to z=(GUARD 0, RETURN
1)}.

name: isolation
doc:
Set (query) the current source isolation mode {to z=(GROUND 0, FLOAT
1)}.

name: output
doc: Set (query) the current source output mode {to z=(OFF 0, ON 1)}.

name: dc_curr
doc:
Set (query) the internally-generated DC current {to f}, in amperes.
The default value is CURR 0.0.

name: comp_volt
doc:
Set (query) the compliance voltage limit {to g}, in volts. The default
value is VOLT 10.0.

name: audible_alarm
doc: Set (query) audible alarms {to z=(OFF 0, ON 1)}.

name: identify
doc: Query the CS580 identification string.

name: token_mode
doc: Set (query) the token response mode {to z=(OFF 0, ON 1)}.

name: op_complete
doc:
The set form, *OPC, will set the OPC bit in the Standard Event Status
register; the query form, *OPC?, will return the value 1.

name: reset
doc: Reset the CS580 to its default configuration.

name: overload
doc:
Reads the current value of the signal overload status. Returns an
integer between 1 and 3 if an overload is detected, or 0 if there is no
overload.

name: status_byte
doc: Reads the Status Byte register [bit i].

name: serv_req_enable
doc: Set (query) the Service Request Enable register [bit i] {to j}.

name: standard_event_status
doc: Reads the Standard Event Status Register [bit i].

name: standard_event_status_enable
doc: Set (query) the Standard Event Status Enable Register [bit i] {to j}.

name: clear_status
doc: *CLS immediately clears the ESR register.

name: last_exec_err
doc:
Query the last execution error code. A query of LEXE? always clears
the error code, so a subsequent LEXE? will return 0.

name: last_comm_err
doc:
Query the last command error code. A query of LCME? always clears
the error code, so a subsequent LCME? will return 0.
